@F TECSL-AR2-T1-31-J1728-CUBE = j-invariant 1728 = sigma(6)^3 = 12^3 ; the j=1728 elliptic curve y^2 = x^3 - x has |E(Q)| = 4 = tau(6), conductor 32 = 2^5, discriminant Δ = 64 = 2^6, automorphism Z/4Z (CM by Z[i]) :: alg-geom/elliptic [10*PASS_LITERATURE]
  => "1728 = 2^6 · 3^3 — exponent 6 itself appears in the prime factorization."
  => "Mordell-Weil rank = 0, torsion Z/2Z × Z/2Z; the four rational points are {∞, (0,0), (1,0), (-1,0)}."
  => "T1-31 entry deepens TECSL-AR-G-ALGGEOM-J1728 (which only stated 1728=σ(6)^3); this entry adds the 4-rational-point and conductor-32 facts."
  |> docs/proofs/T1-31-elliptic-curves.md L1-L80

@F TECSL-AR2-T1-32-MOD-FORMS-DIM = dim M_k(SL_2(Z)) formula has 12 = sigma(6) in its denominator; B_2 = 1/6, B_4 = -1/30 = -1/(5·6), B_6 = 1/42 = 1/(7·6) ; first cusp form Δ ∈ S_12 ; Eisenstein E_12 + Δ basis at weight 12 = sigma(6) :: modular-forms [10*PASS_LITERATURE]
  => "T1-32: σ(6)=12 acts as a STRUCTURAL CONSTANT throughout modular-form theory — dim formula denominator, Bernoulli numerator-6 chain, first cusp form weight, E_4 weight=4=τ(6), E_6 weight=6=n."
  => "von Staudt-Clausen consequence: every Bernoulli denom is a multiple of 6 (already TECSL-AR-G-BASEL-003-BERNOULLI in yesterday's shard) — T1-32 adds the Eisenstein E_k normalisation 1 - (2k/B_k) Σ σ_{k-1}(n) q^n."
  |> docs/proofs/T1-32-modular-forms.md L1-L80

@F TECSL-AR2-T1-33-TRIANGULAR = T(σ(6)-tau(6)) = T(8) = 36 = sigma(6)^2 / 4 (triangular-of-sigma-minus-tau identity not present in T1-29 set) :: number-theory [10]
